SSE sum squared errors defined Equation (10.1), \(n\) number observations, \(p\) number predictors model. RSE provides estimate typical prediction error, smaller values indicating better fit.smaller SSE indicates regression model accurately captures variability response variable, producing better predictions. example, simple linear regression model marketing dataset, SSE 3.3447117^{5}. value represents total squared error predicting revenue spend. closer SSE zero, smaller typical prediction error, indicates higher-quality model.\(R^2\) (R-squared) statistic evaluates well regression model explains variability response variable. defined :\[
